Kirsten M Sandy was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Kirsten M Sandy was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Waiver of Extradition and Order of Remand

Def appears in custody & w/Atty Wilfred deJunco State Public Defenders Office.  Atty Mark D. Bensen for State.  Clerk: EZ.  Defendant understands the Extradition complaint and court finds the person charged is the person in the courtroom and is a fugitive from justice.  Court orders the defendant committed/held in the jail not to exceed 30 days to enable to Governor's warrant.  State believes the defendant is willing to waive extradition.  Atty. deJunco advises the defendant is agreeing to waive extradition to return to New Mexico to present there and defendant signs the extradition waiver.  Court finds the waiver is provided freely, knowingly and intelligently.  Court executes order of remand.
